issue.body:
starting with the longest strings until it's small enough. This way no string gets discarted completely in favor of a longer one before it. Also, the computation happens only if necessary and in the already fork(2)ed child process. The pragmatic implementation doesn't even try to mimic kernels' limits perfectly.

fixes #9340

## Test config

```
object CheckCommand "e2big" {
	var big = " "
	for (i in range(20)) {
		big = big + big
	}
	command = [ "true" ]//, big ]
	env = { "LOLCAT" = big }
}

object Host "e2big" {
	check_command = "e2big"
}
```

### Reproduction before this PR

```
[2023-10-25 12:14:34 +0200] warning/PluginCheckTask: Check command for object 'e2big' (PID: 90872, arguments: 'true') terminated with exit code 128, output: execvpe(true) failed: Argument list too long
```

